e, France":"法国皮卡迪索姆","of Wilton Castle, Herefordshire, England":"英国英格兰賀福爾維爾頓","lifeSummary":"当Margaret Longchamp于1179年出生时，她的父亲Henry de Longchamp Sheriff of Herefordshire19岁，母亲Maud Cantilupe28岁。她和Robert Grelley至少有1个儿子。她去世于1220年在法国皮卡迪索姆享年41岁。"},"hr":{"1179–1220":"1179.–1220.","1177–1210":"1177–1210","1210–1264":"1210–1264","1173–1230":"1173–1230","1210–1262":"1210–1262","1160–1212":"1160–1212.","1151–1246":"1151–1246","1220":"1220.","1264":"1264","1230":"1230","1262":"1262","1151":"1151","1173":"1173","1160":"1160","1246":"1246","1179":"1179.","1212":"1212.","1210":"1210","1177":"1177","about 1210":"oko 1210.","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Francuska","of Wilton Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Wilton, Herefordshire, Engleska, United Kingdom"},"cs":{"1179–1220":"1179–1220","1177–1210":"1177–1210","1210–1264":"1210–1264","1173–1230":"1173–1230","1210–1262":"1210–1262","1160–1212":"1160–1212","1151–1246":"1151–1246","1220":"1220","1264":"1264","1230":"1230","1262":"1262","1151":"1151","1173":"1173","1160":"1160","1246":"1246","1179":"1179","1212":"1212","1210":"1210","1177":"1177","about 1210":"okolo 1210","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Francie","of Wilton Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Wilton, Herefordshire, Anglie, United Kingdom"},"da":{"1179–1220":"1179–1220","1177–1210":"1177–1210","1210–1264":"1210–1264","1173–1230":"1173–1230","1210–1262":"1210–1262","1160–1212":"1160–1212","1151–1246":"1151–1246","1220":"1220","1264":"1264","1230":"1230","1262":"1262","1151":"1151","1173":"1173","1160":"1160","1246":"1246","1179":"1179","1212":"1212","1210":"1210","1177":"1177","about 1210":"omkring 1210","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Frankrig","of Wilton Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Wilton, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom"},"nl":{"1179–1220":"1179–1220","1177–1210":"1177–1210","1210–1264":"1210–1264","1173–1230":"1173–1230","1210–1262":"1210–1262","1160–1212":"1160–1212","1151–1246":"1151–1246","1220":"1220","1264":"1264","1230":"1230","1262":"1262","1151":"1151","1173":"1173","1160":"1160","1246":"1246","1179":"1179","1212":"1212","1210":"1210","1177":"1177","about 1210":"circa 1210","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Frankrijk","of Wilton Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Wilton, Herefordshire, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1179–1220":"1179–1220","1177–1210":"1177–1210","1210–1264":"1210–1264","1173–1230":"1173–1230","1210–1262":"1210–1262","1160–1212":"1160–1212","1151–1246":"1151–1246","1220":"1220","1264":"1264","1230":"1230","1262":"1262","1151":"1151","1173":"1173","1160":"1160","1246":"1246","1179":"1179","1212":"1212","1210":"1210","1177":"1177","about 1210":"about 1210","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, France","of Wilton Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Wilton, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"When Margaret Longchamp was born in 1179, her father, Henry de Longchamp Sheriff of Herefordshire, was 19 and her mother, Maud Cantilupe, was 28. She had at least 1 son with Robert Grelley. She died in 1220, in Somme, Picardie, France, at the age of 41."},"et":{"1179–1220":"1179–1220","1177–1210":"1177–1210","1210–1264":"1210–1264","1173–1230":"1173–1230","1210–1262":"1210–1262","1160–1212":"1160–1212","1151–1246":"1151–1246","1220":"1220","1264":"1264","1230":"1230","1262":"1262","1151":"1151","1173":"1173","1160":"1160","1246":"1246","1179":"1179","1212":"1212","1210":"1210","1177":"1177","about 1210":"umbes 1210","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Prantsusmaa","of Wilton Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Wilton, Herefordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1179–1220":"1179–1220","1177–1210":"1177–1210","1210–1264":"1210–1264","1173–1230":"1173–1230","1210–1262":"1210–1262","1160–1212":"1160–1212","1151–1246":"1151–1246","1220":"1220","1264":"1264","1230":"1230","1262":"1262","1151":"1151","1173":"1173","1160":"1160","1246":"1246","1179":"1179","1212":"1212","1210":"1210","1177":"1177","about 1210":"noin 1210","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Ranska","of Wilton Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Wilton, Herefordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1179–1220":"1179–1220","1177–1210":"1177–1210","1210–1264":"1210–1264","1173–1230":"1173–1230","1210–1262":"1210–1262","1160–1212":"1160–1212","1151–1246":"1151–1246","1220":"1220","1264":"1264","1230":"1230","1262":"1262","1151":"1151","1173":"1173","1160":"1160","1246":"1246","1179":"1179","1212":"1212","1210":"1210","1177":"1177","about 1210":"environ 1210","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, France","of Wilton Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Wilton, Herefordshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Margaret Longchamp est née en 1179, son père, Henry de Longchamp Sheriff of Herefordshire, avait 19 ans et sa mère, Maud Cantilupe, avait 28 ans. Elle a eu au moins 1 fils avec Robert Grelley. Elle est décédée en 1220, à Somme, Picardie, France, à l’âge de 41 ans."},"de":{"1179–1220":"1179–1220","1177–1210":"1177–1210","1210–1264":"1210–1264","1173–1230":"1173–1230","1210–1262":"1210–1262","1160–1212":"1160–1212","1151–1246":"1151–1246","1220":"1220","1264":"1264","1230":"1230","1262":"1262","1151":"1151","1173":"1173","1160":"1160","1246":"1246","1179":"1179","1212":"1212","1210":"1210","1177":"1177","about 1210":"um 1210","Somme, Picardie, France":"Somme, Picardie, Frankreich","of Wilton Castle, Herefordshire, England":"Wilton, Herefordshire, England, United Kingdom","lifeSummary":"Als Margaret Longchamp 1179 geboren wurde, war ihr Vater Henry de Longchamp Sheriff of Herefordshire 19 und ihre Mutter Maud Cantilupe 28. Sie hatte mit Robert Grelley mindestens 1 Sohn. Sie s